Mexico Stocks: America Movil, Cemex, Mexichem, OHL Mexico Gain

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 
2011-10-18T22:38:49Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-18/mexico-stocks-america-movil-cemex-mexichem-ohl-mexico-gain.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC index rose 2.6 percent to 35,011.71.  Most Mexican shares followed U.S. stocks higher as optimism
grew over progress on expanding  Europe ’s rescue fund.  America Movil  SAB (AMXL MM), the wireless carrier
controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , advanced 2.7 percent to
15.92 pesos.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, jumped 7.4 percent to 4.81 pesos, recovering some of
yesterday’s 11 percent decline.  Mexichem SAB (MEXCHEM* MM),  Latin America ’s biggest maker
of plastic pipes, gained 6.3 percent to 41.96 pesos.  OHL Mexico SAB (OHLMEX* MM), the Mexican unit of Spanish
construction company Obrascon Huarte Lain SA, gained 3.5 percent
to 22.07 pesos. The company said yesterday third-quarter net
income climbed 25 percent to 1 billion pesos ($74 million).  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
 jlevin20@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
